\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Glossary: \b0 \ \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural \cf0 template: A tree of DOM nodes containing formal references to model variable values that look like: @\{reference\}. The reference may incorporate basic processing of the value as well.\ model: A JavaScript object or array used to populate parts of a template when the template is cloned and made into an instance.\ instance: A copy of a template with formal references to model variable values replaced with the actual values. The created instance is a "view" of the model.\ view: A rendering of a model object for the purposes of user interaction.\ frame: A frame of reference that tracks the current template, instance, and model. Also, the 'frames' variable maintains a cache of name lookups as well as special variable values.\ context: A stack of frames.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1038\cocoasubrtf360 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\qc\pardirnatural
\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Summary of DOM additions: \b0 \ \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural \cf0 Every template acquires an array of references to instances of the template.\ Every instance acquires:\ ... a reference to the template it was created from.\ ... a reference to the model it was created from.\ ... an array of references to instances of its [immediate] sub-templates (named subinstances).\ Parent elements of instances acquire a reference to the collection that was used to create all of the instances appended underneath it.\ All elements created as part of an instance acquire a reference to the instance they belong to.}
